<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="526" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d526">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.84/143: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-03T17:00:00-05:00">March 3, 1937—5
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>26. Your 83, March 3, noon. Department will issue the statement to
                                the press late tomorrow afternoon, but will substitute as second
                                paragraph the phraseology suggested in your 83, March 3, noon.</p>
                            <p>You may communicate this decision to the Minister for Foreign Affairs
                                on the understanding that no publicity will be given the matter
                                prior to publication in the United States.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>